thread.title: Nielsens: 'Truth' starts, 'Fargo' returns

title: Nielsens: 'Truth' starts, 'Fargo' returns
text:
Rachel Bloom, who plays Rebecca Bunch in CW's 'Crazy Ex-Girlfriend,' reclines in the bedroom set of her character. (Photo: Robert Hanashiro, USA TODAY)
CONNECT 27 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Weak starts. NBC comedy Truth Be Told claimed 2.6 million same-day viewers for Friday's opener, less than half the audience for ABC's competing Dr. Ken (5.8 million). CW's Monday duo of Crazy Ex-Girlfriend (899,000) and Jane the Virgin (1.1 million) were also low. NBC's Chicago Fire returned Tuesday with 7.4 million, down from last fall's 9.2 million.
Democratic presidential candidates Bernie Sanders and Hillary Clinton shake hands at the end of the presidential debate in Las Vegas on Oct. 13, 2015. (Photo: Joe Raedle, Getty Images)
Dems debate. The main portion of the first debate among Democratic presidential candidates netted CNN a record 15.8 million viewers Tuesday, still 8 million shy of earlier GOP debates on Fox News.
Patrick Wilson plays Minnesota state trooper Lou Solverson in FX's 'Fargo.' (Photo: Chris Large, FX)
Cable roundup. FX's Fargo claimed 1.6 million viewers for Monday's second-season premiere. Elsewhere, new seasons of Cinemax's The Knick (269,000 Friday), WGN America's Manhattan (265,000 Tuesday) and Comedy Central's Nathan for You (225,000 Thursday) opened modestly in same-day viewing.
